<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Fri, 03 Jul 2026 01:49:37 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>科学家多年来对神秘的海底“麦田圈”感到困惑</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/scientists-were-puzzled-for-years-by-mysterious-seafloor-crop-circles</link><description>&lt;img src="https://politepol.com/fd/NjxHZtldG2if.xml" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 03 Jul 2026 01:49:35 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/scientists-were-puzzled-for-years-by-mysterious-seafloor-crop-circles</guid></item><item><title>合成生物学可能终于准备好解决生命最大的谜团</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/synthetic-biology-may-finally-be-ready-to-solve-lifes-biggest-mystery</link><description>是什么让东西活着？我们根本不知道，但借助 SpudCell，合成生物学家距离给出答案又近了一步，SpudCell 是迄今为止创造人工生命形式的最复杂的尝试&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/synthetic-biology-may-finally-be-ready-to-solve-lifes-biggest-mystery2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 03 Jul 2026 01:34:35 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/synthetic-biology-may-finally-be-ready-to-solve-lifes-biggest-mystery</guid></item><item><title>理论表明，你的意识会随着时间向前或向后跳跃</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/your-consciousness-jumps-forward-and-backward-in-time-theories-suggest</link><description>未来的“你”可能正在悄悄地塑造你的现实。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/your-consciousness-jumps-forward-and-backward-in-time-theories-suggest.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 03 Jul 2026 01:19:35 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/your-consciousness-jumps-forward-and-backward-in-time-theories-suggest</guid></item><item><title>认识罕见的线粒体肌病：对治疗的影响</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/recognizing-a-rare-mitochondrial-myopathy-implications-for-management</link><description>您知道 TK2 缺乏症的早期体征和症状以及何时怀疑它吗？ &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/recognizing-a-rare-mitochondrial-myopathy-implications-for-management.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 03 Jul 2026 01:04:35 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/recognizing-a-rare-mitochondrial-myopathy-implications-for-management</guid></item><item><title>损伤后体内细胞衰老的细胞类型解析转录网络分析</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/cell-type-resolved-transcriptional-network-analysis-of-in-vivo-cellular-senescence-following-injury</link><description>衰老是细胞水平衰老的一个重要表现，是细胞及时受到损伤而引起的。尽管衰老细胞对我们的多细胞体如何衰老具有广泛的影响，但由于其复杂的性质，识别衰老细胞非常具有挑战性：细胞的许多不同方面都受到这种细胞状态的影响。这使得定义帮助我们确定细胞是否衰老的明确标准变得复杂。在本文中，我们提出了一个计算管道，使我们能够识别与衰老相关的一小部分基因。该方法结合了网络研究中常用的两种方法，即群落检测和节点中心性，并将它们应用于从受损后的小鼠肌肉组织中获得的基因表达数据。获得的结果有助于建立复杂细胞状态（例如衰老）的分子相关性。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/cell-type-resolved-transcriptional-network-analysis-of-in-vivo-cellular-senescence-following-injury.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 03 Jul 2026 00:49:35 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/cell-type-resolved-transcriptional-network-analysis-of-in-vivo-cellular-senescence-following-injury</guid></item><item><title>健康和疾病中调节 cGAS/STING 激活的分子机制</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/molecular-mechanisms-regulating-cgas-sting-activation-in-health-and-disease</link><description>2 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/molecular-mechanisms-regulating-cgas-sting-activation-in-health-and-disease.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 03 Jul 2026 00:34:35 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/molecular-mechanisms-regulating-cgas-sting-activation-in-health-and-disease</guid></item><item><title>1 凯斯西储大学克利夫兰诊所勒纳医学院分子医学系，美国俄亥俄州克利夫兰</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/1-department-of-molecular-medicine-cleveland-clinic-lerner-college-of-medicine-of-case-western-reserve-university-cleveland-ohio-usa</link><description>2 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/1-department-of-molecular-medicine-cleveland-clinic-lerner-college-of-medicine-of-case-western-reserve-university-cleveland-ohio-usa.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 03 Jul 2026 00:19:35 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/1-department-of-molecular-medicine-cleveland-clinic-lerner-college-of-medicine-of-case-western-reserve-university-cleveland-ohio-usa</guid></item><item><title>归咎于模型，而不是机器——更好的数据有助于 3D 打印超材料匹配预测</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/blame-the-model-not-the-machine-better-data-helps-3d-printed-metamaterials-match-predictions</link><description>3D 打印等增材制造为设计超材料提供了绝佳的机会：具有工程结构的材料可以实现所需的性能，例如抗振性。然而，一个主要挑战是预测的超材料响应通常无法匹配现实世界的行为。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/blame-the-model-not-the-machine-better-data-helps-3d-printed-metamaterials-match-predictions.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 03 Jul 2026 00:04:35 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/blame-the-model-not-the-machine-better-data-helps-3d-printed-metamaterials-match-predictions</guid></item><item><title>生物标志物匹配的药物组合可缩小临床前模型中的难治性黑色素瘤</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/biomarker-matched-drug-combos-shrink-treatment-resistant-melanoma-in-preclinical-models</link><description>德克萨斯大学 MD 安德森癌症中心的研究人员领导的一项新研究确定了一种根据特定肿瘤生物学定制药物组合的方法，以改善难治性晚期黑色素瘤的治疗效果。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/biomarker-matched-drug-combos-shrink-treatment-resistant-melanoma-in-preclinical-models2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 02 Jul 2026 23:49:35 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/biomarker-matched-drug-combos-shrink-treatment-resistant-melanoma-in-preclinical-models</guid></item><item><title>探索意识理论及其影响</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/explore-consciousness-theories-and-implications</link><description>正是因为幻影原眼是由细胞作为通用 APS 集中诱发的，与特殊感觉信息的所有内容相同，莱布尼茨的“同类只能与同类相互作用”条件被非物质原眼“单子”满足——与笛卡尔的细胞松果体相反。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/explore-consciousness-theories-and-implications.jpg" /&gt; 由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 02 Jul 2026 23:34:35 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/explore-consciousness-theories-and-implications</guid></item></channel></rss>